text:
Questions:
1. How should we handle the `txID`. The SDK is now required to send this value. I assume that the id will be needed for event processing.
     - Should we automatically compute one. 
     - Should we provide a utility to create a unique value that the application could send to the SDK.

2. How should we handle the `chainID`. The SDK is now required to send this value. Where do we get this value. Will the caller know this value.
for `chainID`, i thought it’s still optional until the channel support is operational
<@U13TWBRBL> I vaguely remember <@U0XPR4NP4> mentioning a mandatory test ID till the channel support is in
<@U1KFBBWG1> <@U13Q594J2> the end-to-end flows should work once <https://gerrit.hyperledger.org/r/#/c/2861/> gets merged
